<section xml:id="C10.S18">
<title>Modulus and Phase Functions</title>        
 
<subsection xml:id="C10.S18.SS1">
<title>Definitions</title>        
  
<para xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.s1">
For <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m1">\nu\geq 0</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m2">x&gt;0</Math> <Math equation-number="10.18.1" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E1">M_{\nu}\left(x\right)e^{i\!\theta_{\nu}\left(x\right)}={H^{(1)}_{\nu}}\left(x \right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="10.18.2" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E2">N_{\nu}\left(x\right)e^{i\!\phi_{\nu}\left(x\right)}={H^{(1)}_{\nu}}'\left(x \right),</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m3">M_{\nu}\left(x\right)</Math> <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m4">(&gt;0)</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m5">N_{\nu}\left(x\right)</Math> <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m6">(&gt;0)</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m7">\theta_{\nu}\left(x\right)</Math> , and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m8">\phi_{\nu}\left(x\right)</Math> are continuous real functions of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m9">\nu</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m10">x</Math> , with the branches of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m11">\theta_{\nu}\left(x\right)</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS1.p1.m12">\phi_{\nu}\left(x\right)</Math> fixed by <Math equation-number="10.18.3" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E3">\theta_{\nu}\left(x\right)\to-\tfrac{1}{2}\pi,\phi_{\nu}\left(x\right)\to\tfrac{1}{2}\pi, , if x\to 0+</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C10.S18.SS2">
<title>Basic Properties</title>        
 
 
<para xml:id="C10.S18.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C10.S18.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="10.18.4" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E4">J_{\nu}\left(x\right)=M_{\nu}\left(x\right)\cos\theta_{\nu}\left(x\right),Y_{\nu}\left(x\right)=M_{\nu}\left(x\right)\sin\theta_{\nu}\left(x\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="10.18.5" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E5">J_{\nu}'\left(x\right)=N_{\nu}\left(x\right)\cos\phi_{\nu}\left(x\right),Y_{\nu}'\left(x\right)=N_{\nu}\left(x\right)\sin\phi_{\nu}\left(x\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="10.18.6" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E6">M_{\nu}\left(x\right)=\left({J_{\nu}^{2}}\left(x\right)+{Y_{\nu}^{2}}\left(x \right)\right)^{\frac{1}{2}},N_{\nu}\left(x\right)=\left({J_{\nu}'^{2}}\left(x\right)+{Y_{\nu}'^{2}}\left(x \right)\right)^{\frac{1}{2}},</Math> <Math equation-number="10.18.7" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E7">\theta_{\nu}\left(x\right)=\operatorname{Arctan}\left(Y_{\nu}\left(x\right)/J_ {\nu}\left(x\right)\right),\phi_{\nu}\left(x\right)=\operatorname{Arctan}\left(Y_{\nu}'\left(x\right)/J_{ \nu}'\left(x\right)\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C10.S18.SS2.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="10.18.8" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E8">{M_{\nu}^{2}}\left(x\right)\theta_{\nu}'\left(x\right)=\frac{2}{\pi x},{N_{\nu}^{2}}\left(x\right)\phi_{\nu}'\left(x\right)=\frac{2(x^{2}-\nu^{2})}{ \pi x^{3}},</Math> <Math equation-number="10.18.9" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E9">{N_{\nu}^{2}}\left(x\right)={M_{\nu}'^{2}}\left(x\right)+{M_{\nu}^{2}}\left(x \right){\theta_{\nu}'^{2}}\left(x\right)={M_{\nu}'^{2}}\left(x\right)+\frac{4} {(\pi xM_{\nu}\left(x\right))^{2}},</Math> <Math equation-number="10.18.10" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E10">(x^{2}-\nu^{2})M_{\nu}\left(x\right)M_{\nu}'\left(x\right)+x^{2}N_{\nu}\left(x \right)N_{\nu}'\left(x\right)+x{N_{\nu}^{2}}\left(x\right)=0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C10.S18.SS2.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="10.18.11" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E11">\tan\left(\phi_{\nu}\left(x\right)-\theta_{\nu}\left(x\right)\right)=\frac{M_{ \nu}\left(x\right)\theta_{\nu}'\left(x\right)}{M_{\nu}'\left(x\right)}=\frac{2 }{\pi xM_{\nu}\left(x\right)M_{\nu}'\left(x\right)},</Math> <Math equation-number="10.18.12" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E12">M_{\nu}\left(x\right)N_{\nu}\left(x\right)\sin\left(\phi_{\nu}\left(x\right)- \theta_{\nu}\left(x\right)\right)=\frac{2}{\pi x}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C10.S18.SS2.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="10.18.13" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E13">x^{2}M_{\nu}''\left(x\right)+xM_{\nu}'\left(x\right)+(x^{2}-\nu^{2})M_{\nu} \left(x\right)=\frac{4}{\pi^{2}{{M_{\nu}^{3}}(x)}},</Math> <Math equation-number="10.18.14" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E14">w^{\prime\prime}+\left(1+\frac{\frac{1}{4}-\nu^{2}}{x^{2}}\right)w=\frac{4}{ \pi^{2}w^{3}}, if w=x^{\frac{1}{2}}M_{\nu}\left(x\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="10.18.15" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E15">x^{3}w^{\prime\prime\prime}+x(4x^{2}+1-4\nu^{2})w^{\prime}+(4\nu^{2}-1)w=0, if w=x{M_{\nu}^{2}}\left(x\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C10.S18.SS2.p1.s5">
<Math equation-number="10.18.16" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E16">{\theta_{\nu}'^{2}}\left(x\right)+\frac{1}{2}\frac{\theta_{\nu}'''\left(x \right)}{\theta_{\nu}'\left(x\right)}-\frac{3}{4}\left(\frac{\theta_{\nu}'' \left(x\right)}{\theta_{\nu}'\left(x\right)}\right)^{2}=1-\frac{\nu^{2}-\tfrac {1}{4}}{x^{2}}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

  
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C10.S18.SS3">
<title>Asymptotic Expansions for Large Argument</title>        
  
<para xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p1.s1">
As <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p1.m1">x\to\infty</Math> , with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p1.m2">\nu</Math> fixed and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p1.m3">\mu=4\nu^{2}</Math> ,
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p2.s1">
 <Math equation-number="10.18.17" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E17">{M_{\nu}^{2}}\left(x\right)\sim\frac{2}{\pi x}\left(1+\frac{1}{2}\frac{\mu-1}{ (2x)^{2}}+\frac{1\cdot 3}{2\cdot 4}\frac{(\mu-1)(\mu-9)}{(2x)^{4}}+\frac{1 \cdot 3\cdot 5}{2\cdot 4\cdot 6}\frac{(\mu-1)(\mu-9)(\mu-25)}{(2x)^{6}}+\cdots \right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="10.18.18" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E18">\theta_{\nu}\left(x\right)\sim x-\left(\frac{1}{2}\nu+\frac{1}{4}\right)\pi+ \frac{\mu-1}{2(4x)}+\frac{(\mu-1)(\mu-25)}{6(4x)^{3}}+\frac{(\mu-1)(\mu^{2}-11 4\mu+1073)}{5(4x)^{5}}+\frac{(\mu-1)(5\mu^{3}-1535\mu^{2}+54703\mu-3\;75733)}{ 14(4x)^{7}}+\cdots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p2.s2">
Also, <Math equation-number="10.18.19" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E19">{N_{\nu}^{2}}\left(x\right)\sim\frac{2}{\pi x}\left(1-\frac{1}{2}\frac{\mu-3}{ (2x)^{2}}-\frac{1}{2\cdot 4}\frac{(\mu-1)(\mu-45)}{(2x)^{4}}-\cdots\right),</Math> the general term in this expansion being <Math equation-number="10.18.20" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E20">-\frac{(2k-3)!!}{(2k)!!}\frac{(\mu-1)(\mu-9)\cdots(\mu-(2k-3)^{2})(\mu-(2k+1)( 2k-1)^{2})}{(2x)^{2k}}, if k\geq 2,</Math> and <Math equation-number="10.18.21" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S18.E21">\phi_{\nu}\left(x\right)\sim x-\left(\frac{1}{2}\nu-\frac{1}{4}\right)\pi+ \frac{\mu+3}{2(4x)}+\frac{\mu^{2}+46\mu-63}{6(4x)^{3}}+\frac{\mu^{3}+185\mu^{2 }-2053\mu+1899}{5(4x)^{5}}+\cdots</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p3.s1">
The remainder after <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p3.m1">k</Math> terms in (10.18.17) does not exceed the <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p3.m2">(k+1)</Math> th term in absolute value and is of the same sign, provided that <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S18.SS3.p3.m3">k&gt;\nu-\tfrac{1}{2}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
  
 
</subsection>
 
</section>
